<dl id="n16012a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16012a">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16012a"> 12(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ skin of beast / at tomb</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">I determined, however, to confirm this intelligent forecast by consulting Tantalus himself. To consult the oracle of a dead hero, it was, I knew, only necessary to undergo the process of &lsquo;incubation,&rsquo; a sort of camping out <mark>on his tomb, in the skin of a sacrificial beast</mark>; and fortunately the tomb of Tantalus had just been discovered in Phrygia by the archaeologists of the British School at Athens. <small> F.C.S. Schiller, <a name="TANT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TANT"><cite title="source">Tantalus</cite></a> (1924) 8</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02134a" href="c02all.htm#c02134a">VI.C.02:134(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
